licit. The lack of explicit reliability is a gap. However, the positive crew aspects may offset communication difficulty? The egocentric and not willing to further education are concerning for long-term.\n\nCandidate D: problem solving, concentration, responsibility, adequate response to unexpected events. Negatives: moody, loner, no calmness, no reliability explicit. Likely less suitable.\n\nThus B seems strongest on reliability and calmness, which are top criteria. The teamwork issues are serious but maybe less than lacking reliability. So I think we should vote for B.\n\nWe should also maybe ask other agents if they have any explicit positive teamwork statements for B, but we already have negative statements. Could ask if any agent has any positive statements about B's teamwork. But we can also just proceed.\n\nGiven the instruction: \"When reading the discussion history, if you see a question another agent asked that you can answer from your own information, include that answer in your public contribution \u2014 even if you were not directly asked.\" There is a question from Agent 1 to Agent 2 about explicit statements about B's teamwork/communication, which we answered earlier. So we have already contributed that. Now we need to produce our own public contribution and vote.\n\nWe should also consider asking about any explicit statements about Candidate C's willingness to further education (we have that) and about any positive teamwork for D. But we have all.\n\nThus produce final public message summarizing reasoning and vote for B."}
